-- Inheritance: A mechanism where one class acquires the properties
and behaviours of another class.

-- Method overriding: When a Child class provides a specific implementation for a
method that is already defined in its Parent class.

-- why it is used?
-- code usability: you write common logic once in the Parent and all children get it for free.

-- Specialization: create category in parent
and then make or customized it specially in the child class.

Single: You copy a template once.

Multilevel: You copy a copy of a copy.

Hierarchical: You use one template to make five different types of forms.

Multiple: Trying to merge two completely different templates into one—Java says "No, that's too confusing!"

